                                    ],
                                    "type": "text",
                                    "content": "finite automata [7, 14]. One of the most famous longstanding open problems in automata theory, known as Cern√Ω Conjecture, states that for a given synchronizing DFA with "
                                },
                                {
                                    "bbox": [
                                        553,
                                        518,
                                        1994,
                                        920
                                    ],
                                    "type": "inline_equation",
                                    "content": "n"
                                },
                                {
                                    "bbox": [
                                        553,
                                        518,
                                        1994,
                                        920
                                    ],
                                    "type": "text",
                                    "content": " states one can always find a synchronizing word of length at most "
                                },
                                {
                                    "bbox": [
                                        553,
                                        518,
                                        1994,
                                        920
                                    ],
                                    "type": "inline_equation",
                                    "content": "(n - 1)^2"
                                },
                                {
                                    "bbox": [
                                        553,
                                        518,
                                        1994,
                                        920
                                    ],
                                    "type": "text",
                                    "content": ". This conjecture was proven for numerous classes of automata, but the problem is still not solved in general case. The concept of synchronization has been also considered in coding theory [3, 8], parts orienting in manufacturing [5, 15], testing of reactive systems [19] and Markov Decision Processes [11, 12]."
                                }
                            ]
                        }
                    ],
                    "index": 0
                },
                {
                    "bbox": [
