                                        1994,
                                        1867
                                    ],
                                    "type": "text",
                                    "content": "In this paper we present a public key cryptosystem utilizing fact, that checking if the PFA is carefully synchronizing is PSPACE- complete. This is however not the first attempt of trying to develop asymmetric cryptosystems with the notion of finite automata. Public key cryptography on finite automata with output is discussed in [21] and uses the notion of invertible automata to provide the hard computational problem, inevitable to design such cryptosystem."
                                }
                            ]
                        }
